ating-stars"><div class="pr-star-v4 pr-star-v4-100-filled"></div><div class="pr-star-v4 pr-star-v4-100-filled"></div><div class="pr-star-v4 pr-star-v4-100-filled"></div><div class="pr-star-v4 pr-star-v4-100-filled"></div><div class="pr-star-v4 pr-star-v4-0-filled"></div></div><div aria-hidden="true" class="pr-snippet-rating-decimal">4</div></div></div><h2 class="pr-faceoff-title" id="pr-bsz02vhTjAqbhoXmwXcop">Familiar</h2><p class="pr-faceoff-review">I really liked this moisturizer. It has a light clean fragrance, and it left my skin feeling super soft and hydrated. It feels extremely familiar to me, and it dawned on me why. I have a jar of of Neutregena HydraBoost gel, so I set them side by side with eachother. It's nearly identical. Even the f...<span id="pr-vvlyxtmXyTobk7ew6JmIp" tabindex="-1" style="display: none;">resh clean fragrance is very similar. Both of these moisturizers perform EXACTLY the same. The only slight difference that I noticed between the two, was Belif Tru Cream Aqua Bomb did make me break out a tad. Nothing major, but I did get a couple tiny whiteheads around my T- Zone. Neutregena has never given me that problem, and has been my go to moisturizer, because it doesn't break me out. I would still use the Belif, it preformed exactly the same as the HydraBoost, and the little breakout was nothing to be alarmed about, and it definitely wouldn't detour me from using the product. I love both! I will use both. This is good to know, in case the retailer doesn't have one or the other, now I have a substitute for each one. Could possibly be a dupe also. I received the Belif True Cream Aqua Bomb from BzzAgent for free, in exchange for my honest opinion, so I don't know the price up front.</span></p><button type="button" class="pr-faceoff-readcomplete" aria-controls="pr-vvlyxtmXyTobk7ew6JmIp" aria-expanded="false" aria-describedby="pr-bsz02vhTjAqbhoXmwXcop">Read complete review<span class="pr-caret-icon"><svg viewBox="-9 -10 52 52" focusable="false" aria-hidden="true"><g><polyline class="pr-caret-icon__line" fill="none" stroke="#333" stroke-width="4" points="23.7,31.5 8.3,16 23.7,0.5 "></polyline></g></svg></span></button></section><div class="pr-faceoff-img"><span class="pr-accessible-text">Versus</span><span class="pr-faceoff-img-txt" aria-hidden="true">VS</span></div><section class="pr-faceoff-negative"><h1 class="pr-faceoff-label">Most Liked Negative Review</h1><div><div class="pr-snippet-stars pr-snippet-stars-png" role="img" aria-label="Rated 3 out of 5 stars"><div aria-hidden="true" class="pr-rating-stars"><div class="pr-star-v4 pr-star-v4-100-filled"></div><div class="pr-star-v4 pr-star-v4-100-filled"></div><div class="pr-star-v4 pr-star-v4-100-filled"></div><div class="pr-star-v4 pr-star-v4-0-filled"></div><div class="pr-star-v4 pr-star-v4-0-filled"></div></div><div aria-hidden="true" class="pr-snippet-rating-decimal">3</div></div></div><h2 class="pr-faceoff-title" id="pr-siynVPzKHWZR6bGJZn0ZI">Great feel, cant get past the smell</h2><p class="pr-faceoff-review">I started using this product on my face in the evening and in the mornings. After the first day, I did notice some skin irritation, minor breakout, but it did not continue and resolved, I think my skin was getting used to the product. Loved the feel, definitely made my skin feel sheer and moisturize...<span id="pr-xehNQgf0PzjZxM-dWCJX6" tabindex="-1" style="display: none;">d. I also really liked the packaging surprisingly, the lid of the container had a lip that made it easier to open, small detail but definitely noticed! 

